# BDD feature sources and the generated behavior contract must stay LF so
# `bdd:export` (gherkin-v39) is deterministic across OS. This repo uses
# core.autocrlf=true, which would otherwise check out *.feature as CRLF on
# Windows and make the regenerated NDJSON drift from the committed LF version,
# blocking the pre-commit bdd:export freshness gate.
*.feature text eol=lf
bdd/behavior-contracts.ndjson text eol=lf

# husky v9 runs hooks through `sh -e`; they must stay LF or a CRLF checkout
# reintroduces the shell syntax error this commit fixes.
.husky/* text eol=lf
